    "updated_at": "2016-12-19T19:15:59Z",
    "body": "I assume we don't usually see this because `create-dist.py` is normally run in a context that has already run the linter.\r\n\r\nWould something like this do the trick?\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"scripts\": {\r\n  \"dist\": \"npm run lint && ./script/create-dist.py\",\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlternatively, we could wrap the `copy_api_json_schema` function in a conditional.. only copy the file if it exists."
